# Cline Rules for `download-cartoons-online`

## Purpose
These rules define contribution standards for AI/code-assist changes in this repository.

## Technology Baseline
- Language: Java 21
- Build Tool: Gradle (Groovy DSL)
- Framework: Spring Context/Core (non-Spring Boot)
- Parsing/HTTP: Jsoup, Apache HttpClient 5
- Testing: JUnit 5 + Mockito

## Coding Standards
- Keep package structure under `dev.harimohan.app.toondownload`.
- Prefer small, focused classes and methods.
- Preserve existing logging style (`slf4j` with parameterized or formatted messages).
- Avoid introducing new frameworks unless explicitly requested.
- Keep changes backward-compatible with current configuration keys.

## Configuration Standards
- All runtime configuration must stay externalized in `application.properties`.
- Do not hardcode environment-specific paths in source code.
- For new properties, document defaults and expected format in `README.md`.

## Testing Standards
- Add/adjust tests for behavior changes in `src/test/java`.
- Prefer deterministic tests with mocks for network-related behavior.
- Ensure tests pass via:
  - `gradlew.bat test` (Windows)
  - `./gradlew test` (Linux/macOS)

## Documentation Standards
- Update `README.md` when behavior/configuration/setup changes.
- Keep examples aligned with current source and Gradle setup.

## Safety & Maintenance
- Never commit secrets, tokens, or private URLs.
- Do not remove existing functionality unless requested.
- Keep dependency updates minimal and justified.
